          {
            "commit": "e32437a8725cb8d78dc68f68a8d4b17583abd5b9",
            "subject": "LU-957 scrub: Proc interfaces and tests for OI scrub"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "yong.fan@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-07-01 02:16:10.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Lai Siyao",
          "email": "laisiyao@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-11-20 08:34:57.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-957 lfsck: LFSCK main engine",
        "message": "LU-957 lfsck: LFSCK main engine\n\nBackport commit: If1bd3cfac1f299e964c029e5e9c4cce6432edfa5\n\nImplement the main engine for Lustre online fsck. The kernel\nthread \"lfsck\" scans the system object table by low layer DT\niteration APIs, and will drives registered scrub component(s)\nto check/repair Lustre system.\n\nIt is the controller for the whole LFSCK, and controls the\nspeed, including the low layer OI scrub (for osd-ldiskfs).\n\nFor urgent mode, like MDT is restored from file-level backup\nagainst ldiskfs, the OI files are invalided. Under such case,\nwe need to rebuild the OI files ASAP, then low layer OI scrub\ninside osd-ldiskfs ignores the main engine speed control, and\nruns with full speed.\n\nSigned-off-by: Lai Siyao <laisiyao@whamcloud.com>\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <yong.fan@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I3d454670960028fcf6b33a9bd14dfa7190a4b1e1\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_1"
    }
  },
